{{Nihongo|'''Hachioji Velodrome'''|八王子自転車競技場|Hachiōji Jitenshakyōgijō}} was a temporary [[velodrome]] located in the [[Hachiōji, Tokyo]] area. Constructed between March and August 1964, it hosted the [[Cycling at the 1964 Summer Olympics|track cycling]] events for the [[1964 Summer Olympics]].  The site of the velodrome was later converted to a public park called Ryonan Park.

