[[File:Keistuoliu Teatras (2008-09-07)1.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Keistuolių Teatras, 2008]]
'''Keistuolių Teatras''' ("Weirdos' Theatre", "Theatre of Eccentric Men") is a [[Lithuania]]n theatre troupe. It was founded in 1989 by actors [[Ilona Balsytė]], [[Aidas Giniotis]] and [[Sigutis Jačėnas]] and [[theatre director]] [[Romualdas Vikšraitis]].<ref>[http://www.keistuoliai.lt/kronika Keistuolių Teatre timeline]</ref> The theatre produces plays and music for general public and children.

In 1999 the theatre became a member of [[ASSITEJ]].

In 20 years (1989–2009) the theatre released 50 plays, 8 videofilms, 11 audiocassetes and 10 CDs.<ref>[http://pramogos.delfi.lt/culture/dvidesimtmecio-proga-keistuoliu-teatras-dovanos-koncertus.d?id=19312092 "Dvidešimtmečio proga Keistuolių teatras dovanos koncertus"] 20th Anniversary Concert of Keistuolių Theatre</ref>

In 2004 it was entered into the ''[[Book of Lithuanian Records]]'' ("Lietuvos rekordų knyga") as the longest time acting private theatre and the theatre with most performances in a year (217).<ref>[http://www.15min.lt/zyme/keistuoliu-teatras Keistuolių Teatras feed] at 15min.lt</ref>

